FBIS4-1233 "drafr079_c_94067" FBIS-AFR-94-079 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 REPUBLIC OF SOUTH AFRICA Finland's President To Attend Inauguration Finland's President To Attend Inauguration MB2204094494 Johannesburg SAPA in English 0901 GMT 22 Apr 94 MB2204094494 Johannesburg SAPA English BFN [Report by E van Wyk] [Text] Pretoria April 22 SAPA -- Finland's newly elected President Mr Martti Ahtisaari plans to attend the inauguration of South Africa's new president in Pretoria on May 10, the Finland Embassy said on Friday. Mr Ahtisaari, a former career diplomat and a former director-general of the Finnish Foreign Affairs Ministry, was for years closely connected with southern Africa. "His role in the developments leading to Namibia's independence was a particularly difficult one," the embassy statement said. Mr Ahtisaari was at the time the special representative of the United Nations secretary-general for Namibia.
